briefTitle: MT10109L in the Long-term, Open-label Treatment of Glabellar Lines (GL) and Lateral Canthal Lines (LCL)

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants Who Experienced Any Adverse Event (AE)
outcomeMeasures.description: The safety analyses were conducted in the Intent-to-Treat (ITT) population. All adverse events were collected from the signing of the ICF to 30 days after the participant's last study visit.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants Who Experienced Treatment-Related Adverse Events (TEAEs)
outcomeMeasures.description: This section focuses primarily on Treatment-Related (Study drug or procedure) Adverse Events(TEAEs). TEAEs are AEs with onset date on or after first dose of study intervention (placebo or MT10109L) in the pivotal study and â‰¤ 30 days after the study exit visit in the extension study.

outcomeMeasures.title: Mean Change From Baseline in Pulse Rate (Beats Per Minute)
outcomeMeasures.description: The outcome reported here is the mean change in pulse rate from baseline to study exit.

outcomeMeasures.title: Mean Change From Baseline in Systolic Blood Pressure (mm Hg)
outcomeMeasures.description: The outcome reported here is the mean change in Systolic BP from baseline to study exit.

outcomeMeasures.title: Mean Change From Baseline in Diastolic Blood Pressure (mm Hg)
outcomeMeasures.description: The outcome reported here is the mean change in Diastolic BP from baseline to study exit.

outcomeMeasures.title: Mean Change From Baseline in Respiratory Rate (Breaths Per Minute)
outcomeMeasures.description: The outcome reported here is the mean change in respiratory rate from baseline to study exit.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Participants With Binding and Neutralizing Antibodies
outcomeMeasures.description: Only samples that tested positive in the binding antibody confirmatory assay were evaluated for neutralizing antibodies. The participants with positive neutralizing antibodies are only shown.
